==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firefly luciferin
<hw>Fire"fly` lu*cif"er*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Biochem.)</fld> <def>a type of <er>luciferin</er> produced by the
firefly <spn>Photinus pyralis</spn>.</def> <note>Its structure has been
elucidated, and chemically it is recognized as
<chname>4,5-Dihydro-2-(6-hydroxy-2-benzothiazol-2-yl)-4-thiazolecarboxylic
acid</chname>, <chform>C11H8N3O2S2</chform>. It has found use in a very
sensitive assay for ATP, in which concentrations of ATP as low as
10<exp>-11</exp> molar can be detected. <au>[MI11]</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>firehouse</ent>⟦br⟧
